\displaystyle \lim_{r \rightarrow 1} \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} r^{2^n}= \infty
r
0 < r < 1
\sum_{n=1}^\infty r^{2^n} > \sum_{n=1}^k r^{2^n} > k\cdot r^{2^k}
k \geqslant 1
r^{2^k} \geqslant \frac12
\geqslant \frac{k}{2}
\sum_{n=1}^\infty r^{(n^2)}>\sum_{n=1}^\infty r^{2n}=\frac{1}{1-r^2}-1=\frac{1}{1-r}\left(\frac{r^2}{1+r}\right).
